Route network

Based on forecasts, the airlines load-factor policy, and marketing analysis, our airline (IATA code: RF) has proposed providing three daily round-trip flights from YVR to LAX, MCO, SLC, YLW, YXC, YXE and ZIH.

With a route network like:

We have two types of fleet, namely Airbus A320 and Airbus A340-500. The seating capacities for these two fleet types are 197 and 237 seats respectively. Furthermore, we have the following information for this airline:

  • Cost per available seat kilometer (CASK) for A320 and A340-500 are 0.038 (3.8 cents) and 0.041 (4.1 cents) respectively.
  • Revenue per available seat kilometer (RASK) for A320 and A340-500 are 0.128 (12.8 cents) and 0.128 (12.8 cents) respectively.

Assume that we have 6 and 9 aircrafts in our A320 and A340-500 fleets, respectively. Due to the small size of our airline we are unable to recapture passengers that were spilled. Also assume turnaround times of 40 and 55 minutes for these two fleet types respectively. Furthermore, sit-connection times for crew members will range from 20 to 170 minutes for A320 and 15 to 180 minutes for A340-500.
